 is safe to assume, is starting out well behind Snowflake as far as capabil=
ities are concerned, but with conversation AI infused into the product from=
 the beginning, while DataBricks has developed its own LLM ( https://www.da=
tabricks.com/blog/2023/04/12/dolly-first-open-commercially-viable-instructi=
on-tuned-llm ). To that end, acquiring engineers who are already focused on=
 LLM interfaces seems like a reasonable defensive move by Snowflake.

Uber and Waymo, Finally
-----------------------

From The Verge ( https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/23/23733547/uber-waymo-rob=
otaxi-phoenix-delivery-autonomous-ridehail ) :

Waymo=E2=80=99s robotaxis will be available to hail for rides and food deli=
very on Uber=E2=80=99s app in Phoenix later this year, the result of a new =
partnership that the two former rivals announced today. A =E2=80=9Cset numb=
er=E2=80=9D of Waymo vehicles will be available to Uber riders and Uber Eat=
s delivery customers in Phoenix, where the Alphabet company recently double=
d its service area to 180 square miles. The partnership was described as =
=E2=80=9Cmulti-year,=E2=80=9D with the goal of bringing together =E2=80=9CW=
aymo=E2=80=99s world-leading autonomous driving technology with the massive=
 scale of Uber=E2=80=99s ridesharing and delivery networks.=E2=80=9D

Speaking of examples, this is a very good one in terms of how long it can t=
